President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. 

1. John R. Bass of New York is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan. Bass is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been an American diplomat since 1988. He is currently serving as Ambassador to the Republic of Turkey.

2. Michael James Dodman of New York is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Islamic Republic of Mauritania. Dodman is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been a career diplomat since 1987. He is currently the Executive Assistant in the Office of the Under Secretary for Economic Growth, Energy and the Environment at the Department of State.

3. C. J. Mahoney of Kansas is nominated to be Deputy United States Trade Representative, with a focus on investment, services, labor, environment, Africa, China, and the Western Hemisphere. Mahoney is a partner at Williams & Connolly LLP, specializing in international disputes and arbitration. He has clerked at the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and the Supreme Court of the United States.

4. Michele Jeanne Sison of Maryland is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Haiti. Sison is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been an American diplomat since 1982. She currently serves as Deputy Permanent Representative at the U.S. Mission to the United Nations in New York.

In addition to the nominations, President Trump also announced his intent to appoint several individuals as members of the Federal Service Impasses Panel.